properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 17 at 1:34PM PST until January 18 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected with total snow accumulation of 10 to
20 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including Maple Falls, the Mount Baker Ski Area,
Newhalem, Lyman, and Concrete, Cascade mountains and valleys
of Snohomish and King Counties, including Darrington, Index,
Skykomish, Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade
mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis Counties, including
the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier,
Ashford, Randle, and Packwood.

* WHEN...From 10 PM this evening to 4 PM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow level will rise from below 1000
feet this evening to around 2500 feet Saturday.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency. Carry chains. Delays are
possible.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 PM PST SATURDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
